main event: An aircraft crew observed two flying objects in the vicinity while flying over the Atlantic Ocean.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a total of 15 minutes,The navigator and crew noted the positions of the objects relative to their aircraft,One object was moving at an angle of 90 degrees, while the other was at 110 degrees,The objects seemed to be separated by approximately 20002 units,There were also streaks of smoke visible after the first observation.
witness description: navigator and crew of the aircraft
